                    <img src="https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/CPM-80-1.4-2-2.png" alt="CP/M-80 1.4 DIR command screenshot" />
                <p>In the last post, we saw <a href="https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/how-to-experience-86-dos/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">how to experience 86-DOS</a>. 86-DOS was a clone of CP/M. In this tutorial, we are going to use CP/M 1.4. Like 86-DOS, it also requires a special emulator which can be downloaded from here:</p>
