<li><a href="https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/files/CPM80v1.4onwindows.zip">CP/M-80 1.4 for Windows</a></li>
</ul>
<h1>Using CP/M-80 1.4</h1>
<p>It is very easy to start using CP/M-80 1.4. On Linux, extract the above archive and right click on the cpm1.sh file and choose "Run as a Program" or run the shell file the way you run any other shell file. On Windows, extract the above archive and double click the Runme.bat file. The Virtual Machine will start.</p>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/CPM-80-1.4-1.png" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 100vw" srcset="https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/responsive/CPM-80-1.4-1-xs.png 300w ,https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/responsive/CPM-80-1.4-1-sm.png 480w ,https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/responsive/CPM-80-1.4-1-md.png 768w"  alt="CP/M-80 1.4 emulator screenshot" width="834" height="630"></figure>You can enter the DIR command to see a list of files.</p>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/CPM-80-1.4-2.png" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 100vw" srcset="https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/responsive/CPM-80-1.4-2-xs.png 300w ,https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/responsive/CPM-80-1.4-2-sm.png 480w ,https://virtualhub.legacyinstaller.pcriot.com/media/posts/4/responsive/CPM-80-1.4-2-md.png 768w"  alt="CP/M-80 1.4 DIR command screenshot" width="834" height="630"></figure>
<p>That's it! We used CP/M-80 1.4, an operating system launched in 1982 after 40 years (at the time of writing this tutorial).</p>
